messages.message: Anyone know how to access the logs for staging? I don’t see it in my console, not sure if I have access
hey @Aaron Vontell - are you in the instabase-main and looking at logs for cluster-001?
@sudeep is `001` staging? We’re looking for staging logs
yeah 001 is staging and 002 is prod
Dumb question but where do I go to see logs haha

@Aaron Vontell - no worries. you can go to logging from gcloud console.
https://console.cloud.google.com/logs/viewer?project=instabase-main&minLogLevel=0&expandAll=false&timestamp=2019-05-27T16:33:29.786000000Z&customFacets=&limitCustomFacetWidth=true&dateRangeStart=2019-05-27T15:33:31.129Z&dateRangeEnd=2019-05-27T16:33:31.129Z&interval=PT1H&resource=container%2Fcluster_name%2Finstabase-main-prod-001&scrollTimestamp=2019-05-27T16:33:02.428788276Z&logName=projects%2Finstabase-main%2Flogs%2Fapi-server
this link here ^^ will take you to api-server logs for staging, you can switch to other services using the dropdown
